concept teaser video were released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=469&aid=0000488291|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \ud30c\uaca9 \uc0ad\ubc1c \ucf58\uc149\ud2b8\ub85c \uc608\uace0\ud55c \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4\uace1 \u2018\ubc49\uc5b4\u2019|last=Lee|first=Ho-yeon|date=April 17, 2020|accessdate=April 22, 2020|language=ko|work=[[Hankook Ilbo]]|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/RBW_MAMAMOO/status/1250982333626249216|title= 1st Solo Album <SPIT IT OUT>|date=April 17, 2020|accessdate=April 18, 2020|publisher=Mamamoo|via=[[Twitter]]}}</ref> On April 20, the fifth teaser photo and a teaser for the music video of the single were released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0004194248|title='\uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4 D-3' \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, '\ubc49\uc5b4' \ud2f0\uc800 \uacf5\uac1c \"\ud558\uace0 \uc2f6\uc740 \ub300\ub85c \ub2e4 \ud558\uace0 \uc0b4\uc544\"|trans-title='Solo Debut D-3' Mamamu Solar, 'Spit' teaser released \"Do whatever you want and live\"|last=Lee|first=Seunghoon|date=April 22, 2020|accessdate=April 22, 2020|work=OSEN|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> Ahead of the single album release, Solar revealed an interview preview video recorded in the corner of the practice room during the choreography practice, through her official SNS channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=629&aid=0000023536|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c \"\uc194\ub85c\uace1 '\ubc49\uc5b4', \ubd88 \ub9db \uc544\uc774\uc2a4\ud06c\ub9bc \uac19\uc544\"|last=Jeong|first=Byeong-geun|date=April 22, 2020|accessdate=April 22, 2020|work=The Fact|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0004194615|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c \"\uccab \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4\uace1 '\ubc49\uc5b4', \ud3ec\uc778\ud2b8 \ub9ce\uc740 '\ubd88 \ub9db \uc544\uc774\uc2a4\ud06c\ub9bc' \uac19\uc544\"|trans-title=Mamamoo Solar \"The first solo debut song\" Spit \"|last=Lee|first=Seunghoon|date=April 21, 2020|accessdate=April 22, 2020|work=OSEN|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> On April 22, the sixth teaser photo and another teaser for the music video were released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0003557439|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd] '\uc194\ub85c\ub370\ubdd4 D-1' \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uc18d \ub2e4 \ube44\uce58\ub294 '\ube44\ub2d0 \ud328\uc158' \ud2f0\uc800 \uacf5\uac1c|last=Baek|first=Ji-eun|date=April 22, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=Sports Chosun|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\nThe single was released on April 23 with an accompanying music video.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=108&aid=0002858222|last= Lee|first= Jung-ho|script-title=ko: \uc194\ub77c, \ud2f0\uc800\ub9cc\ud07c \ud30c\uaca9\uc801\uc778 \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4 '\ubc49\uc5b4'[6\uc2dc\u2605\uc0b4\ub871]|trans-title=Solar's solo debut as 'teaser' 'spit' [6 o'clock salon]|work=Star Today|accessdate=April 23, 2020|language=Korean|date=April 23, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> The song was written by Solar and Kim Do-hoon and was produced by him alongside rapper [[Sleepy (rapper)|Sleepy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=382&aid=0000815597|last= Jeon|first= Hyojin|script-title=ko: [DA:\uc2e0\uace1] \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c \u2018\ubc49\uc5b4\u2019, \ubbff\ub4e3\u00b7\ubbff\ubcf4 \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4\u2026\uace0\ub9c9\uc5d0 \ub0b4\ub9b0 \uc139\uc2dc\u7f8e|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo|Sports Chosun]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020|language=Korean|date=April 23, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.koreatimes.co.kr/pages/article.asp?newsIdx=288422|last= Lee|first=Gyu-lee|title=MAMAMOO's Solar kicks off solo act with new album|work=[[The Korea Times]]|date=April 23, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref> Solar participated in writing and conceptualizing the entire single album.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0004193960|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4 \uae30\ub300 \ud3ec\uc778\ud2b8 \uc14b #\uccab \ub3c4\uc804 #\ucc9c\uc758 \uc5bc\uad74 #\ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4 \ud038|last=Sun|first= Mi-kyung|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=OSEN|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Spit It Out\" combines [[dark pop]] with [[Latin pop]].<ref name=\"rsindia\">{{cite web|url=https://rollingstoneindia.com/mamamoo-solar-makes-powerful-solo-debut-with-spit-it-out/|last= Chakraborty|first=Riddhi|title=MAMAMOO\u2019s Solar Makes Powerful Solo Debut With \u2018Spit It Out\u2019|work=[[Rolling Stone|Rolling Stone India]]|date=April 23, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref> It has been described as an empowering song built on \"trance sound on top of an energetic beat.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=003&aid=0009829884|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4 \uae30\ub300 \ud3ec\uc778\ud2b8 \uc14b #\uccab \ub3c4\uc804 #\ucc9c\uc758 \uc5bc\uad74 #\ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4 \ud038|last=Lee|first= Jae-hoon|date=April 23, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=Newsis|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> It features latin [[riff|guitar riffs]] which blends with \"unique [[synthesizer|synth sounds]]\" and contains a catchy [[hook (music)|hook]].<ref name\"herald\">{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0003291320|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uc624\ub298 \ub370\ubdd4 \uccab \uc2f1\uae00\uc568\ubc94 \ubc1c\ub9e4\u2026\ubcf8\uaca9 \uc194\ub85c \uc544\ud2f0\uc2a4\ud2b8 \ub3c4\uc57d|trans-title=Mamamu Solar releases its first single album to debut today\u2026 Authentic solo artist leap|date=April 23, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=[[Herald Corporation]]|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> The song uses minimal [[instrumental|instrumentation]] from [[bass guitar|bass]] and [[percussion instrument|percussion]] to highlight the singer's vocals.<ref name=\"rsindia\"/> The lyrics talk about self-confidence and success.<ref name=\"rsindia\"/> According to a press release, the song lyrically \"unleashes the words and actions that Solar wants to say, and expresses the confidence and confident figure that is not bound by other people's standards.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=108&aid=0002858074|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4 \uae30\ub300 \ud3ec\uc778\ud2b8 \uc14b #\uccab \ub3c4\uc804 #\ucc9c\uc758 \uc5bc\uad74 #\ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4 \ud038|trans-title=Mamamu Solar unveils its first single 'spit' after 6 years of debut today (23rd)|last=Han|first=Hae-sun|date=April 23, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=Star Today|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\n==Promotion==\nSolar had her [[Music programs of South Korea#Performances|debut stage]] on the [[Music programs of South Korea|music program]] ''[[M Countdown| M Countdown!]]'' on April 23, 2020 where she performed the song.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000443644|title='\uc5e0\uce74\uc6b4\ud2b8\ub2e4\uc6b4' \uac13\uc138\ube10\u00b7\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c\u00b7\uc5d0\uc774\ud504\ub9b4, \ucef4\ubc31 \ubb34\ub300 \ucd5c\ucd08 \uacf5\uac1c|trans-title='M Countdown' GOT7, Mamamu Solar and April, the first comeback stage|last=Woo|first=Bin|date=April 23, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=[[Hankyung|TenAsia]]|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nA music video, produced by [[Zanybros]], was released simultaneously with the release of the single.<ref name=\"rsindia\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\n;Download and streaming\n* 1. \"Spit it Out\" \n;CD\n* 1. \"Spit it Out\" \n* 2. \"Spit it Out\" (Instrumental)\n\n== Release history ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! Region\n! Date\n! Format\n! Label\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| <!-- Do not change to \"Worldwide\", as no music platform is available in every country -->Various\n| April 23, 2020\n|  {{hlist|[[Music download|Download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]|[[Compact Disc|CD]]}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[RBW (company)|RBW]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n", "text_old": "{{notability|date=April 2020}}\n{{sources|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|2020 single by Solar}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Spit it Out\n| cover      = Solar - Spit it Out.jpg\n| alt        = \n| caption    = Cover of the single\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Solar (singer)| Solar]]\n| language   = {{hlist|Korean|English|}}\n| released   = {{Start date|2020|04|23}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Compact Disc|CD]]|[[Music download|download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| recorded   = 2019 - 2020\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[dark pop]]|[[Latin pop]]}}\n| length     = 3:14\n| label      = {{hlist|[[RBW (company)|RBW]]|}}\n| writer   = Kim Yong-sun - Kim-Do Hoon\n| producer   = {{hlist|Kim-Do Hoon|[[Sleepy (rapper)|Kim Sung-won]]}}\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|79agYOEgKQk|\"Spit it Out\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Spit it Out'''\" ({{ko-hhrm|\ubc49\uc5b4|}}) is the debut solo single by South Korean singer and [[Mamamoo]] member [[Solar (singer)| Solar]], released on April 23, 2020 by [[RBW (company)|RBW]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Baek|first=Ji-eun|script-title=ko: [\uacf5\uc2dd] \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uc624\ub298 '\uc2a4\ud54f\uc787\uc544\uc6c3' \ubc1c\ud45c\u2026\uc194\ub85c \uc544\ud2b8\uc2a4\ud2b8 \ub3c4\uc57d|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0003558010|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo|Sports Chosun]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020|language=Korean|date=April 23, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> The song was written by Solar and Kim Do-hoon, who also produced the single alongside rapper [[Sleepy (rapper)|Sleepy]]. A music video was released simultaneously with the single.\n\n==Background and release==\nOn April 10, [[RBW (company)|RBW]] agency announced that [[Mamamoo]]'s [[Solar (singer)|Solar]] would be making her solo debut with single \"Spit It Out\" on April 23.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mengnews.joins.com/view.aspx?aId=3075941|title=Mamamoo\u2019s Solar set for solo debut|date=April 10, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|last=Yoon |first=So-yeon|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]}}</ref> The first promotional teaser poster for the single was released on the same day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=003&aid=0009808309|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \ub370\ubdd4 6\ub144\ub9cc\uc5d0 \uc194\ub85c\u2026'\uc2a4\ud54f \uc787 \uc544\uc6c3'|date=April 10, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|last=Lee|first=Jaehun|work=Newsis|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> The official cover artwork was finally revealed on April 13.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000442309|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uac70\uce68\uc5c6\ub294 \ub9e4\ub825\u2026\ud0c0\uc774\ud2c0\uace1\uc740 '\ubc49\uc5b4'|trans-title=Mamamu Solar, unstoppable charm ... Title song 'Spit'|last=Woo|first=Bin|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=TenAsia|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0003553863|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd] \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uccab \uc2f1\uae00 \uc568\ubc94 'SPIT IT OUT' 23\uc77c \ubc1c\ud45c\u2026\ud0c0\uc774\ud2c0\uace1 '\ubc49\uc5b4'\ub85c \uac78\ud06c\ub7ec\uc2dc \uc608\uace0|trans-title=[Official] Mamamu Solar announces its first single album 'SPIT IT OUT' on the 23rd\u2026 Girl crush notice with title song 'Spit'|last=Sun|first=Joon|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=Sports Chosun|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> On April 14, the first teaser photo and a 24 second intro teaser video were released through Mamamoo's official [[Social networking service|SNS]] accounts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0004191868|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4\uace1 '\ubc49\uc5b4' \ud2f0\uc800 \uacf5\uac1c...\ud654\ub824+\uac15\ub82c \ud551\uac70\ud301 \ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4|trans-title=Mamamoo Solar unveils solo debut song 'Spit' teaser ... gorgeous + intense fingertip performance|date=April 14, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=OSEN|last=Kyung|first=Jimin|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=469&aid=0000487304|last=Kim|first=Hana|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uac15\ub82c\ud568 \ud3ed\ubc1c \ud551\uac70\ud301 \ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4\u2026\u2018SPIT IT OUT\u2019 \ud30c\uaca9 \ucf58\uc149\ud2b8 \uc608\uace0|trans-title=Mamamoo Solar, Explosive Fingertip Performance\u2026 Announcement on the concept of 'SPIT IT OUT'|date=April 14, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=[[Hankook Ilbo]]|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> On April 15, the second teaser photo was revealed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=421&aid=0004588177|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uccab \uc2f1\uae00 '\uc2a4\ud54f \uc787 \uc544\uc6c3' \ud2f0\uc800\uc774\ubbf8\uc9c0 \uacf5\uac1c\u2026\uace0\ud639\uc801|trans-title=Mamamoo Solar unveils teaser image for its first single 'Spit It Out' Alluring|last=Ahn|first=Tae-hyn|date=April 15, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|language=ko|work=News1|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=144&aid=0000666986|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uccab \uc2f1\uae00 \u2018SPIT IT OUT\u2019 \uac15\ub82c\ud55c \ud2f0\uc800\uc774\ubbf8\uc9c0 \ucd94\uac00 \uacf5\uac1c|last=Lee|first=Yu-jin|date=April 15, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|language=ko|work=Sports World|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> On April 16, the third teaser photo along with a performance version of concept teaser were released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=421&aid=0004591158|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uc790\uc720\ubd84\ubc29 \uafb8\ub7ec\uae30 \ub9e4\ub825\u2026'\ubc49\uc5b4' \ud2f0\uc800 \ucd94\uac00 \uacf5\uac1c|last=Go|first=Seung-ah|date=April 16, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|language=ko|work=News1|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> On April 17, the fourth teaser photo and a special version concept teaser video were released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=469&aid=0000488291|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \ud30c\uaca9 \uc0ad\ubc1c \ucf58\uc149\ud2b8\ub85c \uc608\uace0\ud55c \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4\uace1 \u2018\ubc49\uc5b4\u2019|last=Lee|first=Ho-yeon|date=April 17, 2020|accessdate=April 22, 2020|language=ko|work=[[Hankook Ilbo]]|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/RBW_MAMAMOO/status/1250982333626249216|title= 1st Solo Album <SPIT IT OUT>|date=April 17, 2020|accessdate=April 18, 2020|publisher=Mamamoo|via=[[Twitter]]}}</ref> On April 20, the fifth teaser photo and a teaser for the music video of the single were released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0004194248|title='\uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4 D-3' \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, '\ubc49\uc5b4' \ud2f0\uc800 \uacf5\uac1c \"\ud558\uace0 \uc2f6\uc740 \ub300\ub85c \ub2e4 \ud558\uace0 \uc0b4\uc544\"|trans-title='Solo Debut D-3' Mamamu Solar, 'Spit' teaser released \"Do whatever you want and live\"|last=Lee|first=Seunghoon|date=April 22, 2020|accessdate=April 22, 2020|work=OSEN|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> Ahead of the single album release, Solar revealed an interview preview video recorded in the corner of the practice room during the choreography practice, through her official SNS channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=629&aid=0000023536|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c \"\uc194\ub85c\uace1 '\ubc49\uc5b4', \ubd88 \ub9db \uc544\uc774\uc2a4\ud06c\ub9bc \uac19\uc544\"|last=Jeong|first=Byeong-geun|date=April 22, 2020|accessdate=April 22, 2020|work=The Fact|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0004194615|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c \"\uccab \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4\uace1 '\ubc49\uc5b4', \ud3ec\uc778\ud2b8 \ub9ce\uc740 '\ubd88 \ub9db \uc544\uc774\uc2a4\ud06c\ub9bc' \uac19\uc544\"|trans-title=Mamamoo Solar \"The first solo debut song\" Spit \"|last=Lee|first=Seunghoon|date=April 21, 2020|accessdate=April 22, 2020|work=OSEN|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> On April 22, the sixth teaser photo and another teaser for the music video were released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0003557439|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd] '\uc194\ub85c\ub370\ubdd4 D-1' \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uc18d \ub2e4 \ube44\uce58\ub294 '\ube44\ub2d0 \ud328\uc158' \ud2f0\uc800 \uacf5\uac1c|last=Baek|first=Ji-eun|date=April 22, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=Sports Chosun|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\nThe single was released on April 23 with an accompanying music video.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=108&aid=0002858222|last= Lee|first= Jung-ho|script-title=ko: \uc194\ub77c, \ud2f0\uc800\ub9cc\ud07c \ud30c\uaca9\uc801\uc778 \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4 '\ubc49\uc5b4'[6\uc2dc\u2605\uc0b4\ub871]|trans-title=Solar's solo debut as 'teaser' 'spit' [6 o'clock salon]|work=Star Today|accessdate=April 23, 2020|language=Korean|date=April 23, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> The song was written by Solar and Kim Do-hoon and was produced by him alongside rapper [[Sleepy (rapper)|Sleepy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=382&aid=0000815597|last= Jeon|first= Hyojin|script-title=ko: [DA:\uc2e0\uace1] \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c \u2018\ubc49\uc5b4\u2019, \ubbff\ub4e3\u00b7\ubbff\ubcf4 \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4\u2026\uace0\ub9c9\uc5d0 \ub0b4\ub9b0 \uc139\uc2dc\u7f8e|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo|Sports Chosun]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020|language=Korean|date=April 23, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.koreatimes.co.kr/pages/article.asp?newsIdx=288422|last= Lee|first=Gyu-lee|title=MAMAMOO's Solar kicks off solo act with new album|work=[[The Korea Times]]|date=April 23, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref> Solar participated in writing and conceptualizing the entire single album.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0004193960|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4 \uae30\ub300 \ud3ec\uc778\ud2b8 \uc14b #\uccab \ub3c4\uc804 #\ucc9c\uc758 \uc5bc\uad74 #\ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4 \ud038|last=Sun|first= Mi-kyung|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=OSEN|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Spit it out\" combines [[dark pop]] with [[Latin pop]].<ref name=\"rsindia\">{{cite web|url=https://rollingstoneindia.com/mamamoo-solar-makes-powerful-solo-debut-with-spit-it-out/|last= Chakraborty|first=Riddhi|title=MAMAMOO\u2019s Solar Makes Powerful Solo Debut With \u2018Spit It Out\u2019|work=[[Rolling Stone|Rolling Stone India]]|date=April 23, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref> It has been described as an empowering song built on \"trance sound on top of an energetic beat.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=003&aid=0009829884|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4 \uae30\ub300 \ud3ec\uc778\ud2b8 \uc14b #\uccab \ub3c4\uc804 #\ucc9c\uc758 \uc5bc\uad74 #\ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4 \ud038|last=Lee|first= Jae-hoon|date=April 23, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=Newsis|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> It features latin [[riff|guitar riffs]] which blends with \"unique [[synthesizer|synth sounds]]\" and contains a catchy [[hook (music)|hook]].<ref name\"herald\">{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0003291320|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uc624\ub298 \ub370\ubdd4 \uccab \uc2f1\uae00\uc568\ubc94 \ubc1c\ub9e4\u2026\ubcf8\uaca9 \uc194\ub85c \uc544\ud2f0\uc2a4\ud2b8 \ub3c4\uc57d|trans-title=Mamamu Solar releases its first single album to debut today\u2026 Authentic solo artist leap|date=April 23, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=[[Herald Corporation]]|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> The song uses minimal [[instrumental|instrumentation]] from [[bass guitar|bass]] and [[percussion instrument|percussion]] to highlight the singer's vocals.<ref name=\"rsindia\"/> The lyrics talk about self-confidence and success.<ref name=\"rsindia\"/> According to a press release, the song lyrically \"unleashes the words and actions that Solar wants to say, and expresses the confidence and confident figure that is not bound by other people's standards.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=108&aid=0002858074|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c, \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4 \uae30\ub300 \ud3ec\uc778\ud2b8 \uc14b #\uccab \ub3c4\uc804 #\ucc9c\uc758 \uc5bc\uad74 #\ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4 \ud038|trans-title=Mamamu Solar unveils its first single 'spit' after 6 years of debut today (23rd)|last=Han|first=Hae-sun|date=April 23, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=Star Today|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\n==Promotion==\nSolar had her [[Music programs of South Korea#Performances|debut stage]] on the [[Music programs of South Korea|music program]] ''[[M Countdown| M Countdown!]]'' on April 23, 2020 where she performed the song.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000443644|title='\uc5e0\uce74\uc6b4\ud2b8\ub2e4\uc6b4' \uac13\uc138\ube10\u00b7\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uc194\ub77c\u00b7\uc5d0\uc774\ud504\ub9b4, \ucef4\ubc31 \ubb34\ub300 \ucd5c\ucd08 \uacf5\uac1c|trans-title='M Countdown' GOT7, Mamamu Solar and April, the first comeback stage|last=Woo|first=Bin|date=April 23, 2020|accessdate=April 23, 2020|work=[[Hankyung|TenAsia]]|language=ko|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nA music video, produced by [[Zanybros]], was released simultaneously with the release of the single.<ref name=\"rsindia\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\n;Download and streaming\n* 1. \"Spit it Out\" \n;CD\n* 1. \"Spit it Out\" \n* 2. \"Spit it Out\" (Instrumental)\n\n== Release history ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! Region\n! Date\n! Format\n! Label\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| <!-- Do not change to \"Worldwide\", as no music platform i